ci_support_linux_64_.yaml:
channel_sources:
- conda-forge
channel_targets:
- conda-forge main
docker_image:
- quay.io/condaforge/linux-anvil-x86_64:alma9
python_min:
- '3.10'

about.summary:
modulegraph determines a dependency graph between Python modules primarily
by bytecode analysis for import statements. modulegraph uses similar methods
to modulefinder from the standard library, but uses a more flexible internal
representation, has more extensive knowledge of special cases, and is extensible.

name: modulegraph
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "modulegraph" %}
{% set version = "0.19.7" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 9ad8a81148ba1d90ade66617a153786f7d7cf6a88de83ee28e251183122c2a57

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  entry_points:
    - modulegraph = modulegraph.__main__:main
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python {{ python_min }}
    - setuptools
  run:
    - altgraph >=0.15
    - python >={{ python_min }}
    - setuptools

test:
  imports:
    - modulegraph
  commands:
    - pip check
    - modulegraph --help
  requires:
    - pip
    - python {{ python_min }}

about:
  home: https://pypi.org/project/modulegraph
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: |
    modulegraph determines a dependency graph between Python modules primarily
    by bytecode analysis for import statements. modulegraph uses similar methods
    to modulefinder from the standard library, but uses a more flexible internal
    representation, has more extensive knowledge of special cases, and is extensible.
  dev_url: https://github.com/ronaldoussoren/modulegraph
  doc_url: https://modulegraph.readthedocs.io/en/latest/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bkpoon
